@startuml
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

actor "Player Client" as Client

component "Frontend State" as Front
component "Realtime Gateway" as RT
component "MatchService" as MatchSvc
component "GameRuntimeService" as Runtime
component "Game Module" as GameModule
database "Match Table" as MatchDB
database "MatchAction Table" as ActionDB
database "MatchSnapshot Table" as SnapDB

Client --> Front : user input
Front --> RT : action request
RT --> MatchSvc : submit action
MatchSvc --> Runtime : execute action
Runtime --> GameModule : validate/apply rules
Runtime --> ActionDB : persist action
Runtime --> SnapDB : persist latest snapshot
Runtime --> MatchDB : update current match state
MatchSvc --> RT : accepted/rejected + authoritative result
RT --> Front : authoritative event/state update

note right of Front
Frontend state is ephemeral and optimistic at most.
It is not authoritative.
end note

note right of Runtime
Authoritative gameplay transition happens here.
end note

note right of MatchDB
Current operational state
end note

note right of ActionDB
Full action history
end note

note right of SnapDB
Recovery and fast resync
end note
@enduml
